      "side": 1,
      "message": "MPLS Label based datapath semantics should be used when configured so by the tenant.  Today even for VXLAN enabled networks by the tenant, the labels are generated by L3 Forwarding service andused.  And such labels are re-used for inter-DC use-cases with BGPVPN as well..\n\nThe implementation of this Spec, will completely remove reliance on using labels for L3 Forwarding within the DC.  Instead it will re-use the LPortTags (which is unique for every port in the cloud) to provide L3 Forwarding semantics in the datapath.\n\nMore specifically, the traffic from source VM will be routed in source OVS by the L3VPN pipeline.  After that router, the packet will travel as a switched packet in the VXLAN underlay within the DC.  In the destination OVS, the packet will be collected and sent to the the destination VM through the existing ELAN pipeline.",
